European Coincidental Indicator for September: Summary

-- B y   K r i s t i a n   S i e d e n b u r g
-- 
2011-09-30T07:30:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-30/european-coincidental-indicator-for-september-summary-table-.html
Economic growth in the nations
sharing the euro slowed in September, according to the Eurocoin indicator from
the  Bank of Italy  and the Centre for Economic Policy Research in  London .  The Eurocoin indicator, which draws on  interest rates ,
sentiment surveys and other economic indicators, decreased to
0.03 in September compared to 0.22 the previous month. 
A decrease in the index indicates slower economic growth.  SOURCE: Bank of  Italy  and Centre for Economic Policy Research (CEPR)
 http://eurocoin.bancaditalia.it 
